**Report Structure**

**1. Usage Pattern Analysis**
This WAN link is significantly underutilized, averaging only 0.7% of its 10 Mbps provisioned speed. Business hour usage is also very low. While extreme, short bursts up to 56.56 Mbps occur, sustained daily peaks average only 0.62 Mbps. Overall usage trends are stable with a slight decrease.

**2. Capacity Planning Recommendations**
The link is heavily over-provisioned for current sustained usage. With 99th percentile usage at 0.80 Mbps and sustained daily peaks at 0.62 Mbps, the existing 10 Mbps capacity is far more than required. A lower provisioned speed could be considered for cost optimization, ensuring burst tolerance.

**3. Performance Risks & Bottlenecks**
Despite low average usage, the link experiences very brief, high-intensity bursts exceeding 10 Mbps, reaching 56.56 Mbps. These occurrences are extremely rare (0.10% of time), and the link maintains excellent SLA compliance (99.88%). These bursts are likely handled by the ISP, indicating no consistent bottleneck.

**Conclusion**
The current 10 Mbps capacity is more than sufficient for observed usage, offering significant headroom.
